Vice President Mike Pence and Health and Human Services Secretary Alex Azar have added several individuals to the President's Coronavirus Task Force. The new members include Dr. Ben Carson, Secretary of Housing and Urban Development, Dr. Stephen Hahn, Commissioner of Food and Drugs, and Kelvin Droegemeier, Director of The White House Office of Science and Technology Policy. Last week, Secretary of the Treasury Steven Mnuchin, Surgeon General Dr. Jerome Adams, Director of the National Economic Council Larry Kudlow, and Coronavirus Response Coordinator Dr. Deborah Birx were also added to the task force.